      {
        "id": 3118385,
        "name": "SeanSydney",
        "username": "Sean_S_y_d_n_e_y",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/sean_s_y_d_n_e_y/{size}/3454_2.png",
        "created_at": "2021-03-07T22:05:55.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>As others have noted on Cellartracker, this really, REALLY needs an hour or more of air to get going. Was initially shocked by the orange/peachy colour it poured, and it was grumpy and reticent at first and I honestly didn\u2019t know what to make of it because it seemed so muddled but here follows my notes over the next hour and a bit:</p>\n<p>Nose: Bruised yellow apple. Broad, broad, broad. Lightly oxidative. Mineral, but like\u2026a sheet? Of minerals. Like aged white burg with bubbles. Acid still SO present. Again, that bruised apple. Something lightly spicy on the finish. Depth. Cloves? Non-sugary cinnamon? Just intense, forward, mouth coating. Finish so, so long. Enveloping. This wine is quietly yelling THINK ON ME AWHILE.</p>\n<p>This is a wine that really demands your full attention. Lucky to have had it.</p>",
